ARTICLES['compress-images-web']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-compress-images-web.html',title:'Complete Guide to Image Compression for Web — Faster Loading Pages',date:'June 2026',read:'6 min',cat:'Image Tools',excerpt:'Learn how to compress images for web without losing quality. Covers JPG, PNG, WebP formats, compression tools, and best practices for Core Web Vitals.',html:'<p>Page speed is a Google ranking factor, and images are the biggest culprit. A single uncompressed hero image can add 3–5 seconds to load time. Here is everything you need to know.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/image-compressor" class="tool-cta-link">Compress Images Free →</a>\n<h2>Why image compression matters for SEO</h2>\n<p>Google uses Core Web Vitals — especially Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) — as a ranking signal. LCP measures how long the largest image on screen takes to load. Unoptimised images are the leading cause of poor LCP scores. Compressing images typically improves LCP by 30–60%.</p>\n<h2>Lossy vs lossless — which to use?</h2>\n<p><strong>Lossy compression</strong> removes some image data. At 80–85% quality, the result looks identical to the human eye but is 60–70% smaller. Use lossy for all web photographs.</p>\n<p><strong>Lossless compression</strong> reduces file size without removing any pixels — typically 15–30% savings. Use lossless for logos, icons, and graphics where pixel precision matters.</p>\n<h2>Best quality settings per format</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>JPG</strong>: Quality 80–85% — visually identical to 100%, 60% smaller</li><li><strong>WebP lossy</strong>: Quality 80% — 25% smaller than JPG 85% at the same visual quality</li><li><strong>PNG</strong>: Always lossless — switch to WebP for smaller files</li></ul>\n<h2>Step-by-step compression workflow</h2>\n<ol><li>Resize the image to the actual display size first (never upload a 4000px image that displays at 800px)</li><li>Convert to WebP format using the <a href="/#/t/jpg-to-webp">JPG to WebP converter</a></li><li>Compress at 80% quality using the <a href="/#/t/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a></li><li>Strip EXIF data using the <a href="/#/t/exif-remover">EXIF Remover</a> (saves 50–100KB per photo)</li></ol>\n<h2>Before uploading to your website</h2>\n<p>Run your images through this checklist: dimensions match display size, file is WebP or compressed JPG, EXIF metadata removed, file name uses hyphens not underscores (image-compression-guide.webp not imageCompressionGuide.webp).</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What is the ideal image file size for web?</summary><p>Under 100KB for most images. Hero images can go to 200KB. Thumbnails and icons should be under 30KB. Use the <a href="/#/t/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a> to target these sizes.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Does compression affect image quality?</summary><p>At 80–85% quality, no visible difference exists. Only when you go below 70% do compression artifacts become noticeable — blocky areas, colour banding in gradients.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Should I compress PNG files?</summary><p>Use lossless PNG compression for graphics, or switch to WebP for best results. Lossy PNG compression causes visible colour banding on flat-colour images.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['remove-background-image-free']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-remove-background-image-free.html',title:'How to Remove Background From Image Free Online (No Photoshop)',date:'June 2026',read:'4 min',cat:'Image Tools',excerpt:'Remove image backgrounds online for free without Photoshop. Works for product photos, profile pictures, logos and more. Browser-based, no uploads.',html:'<p>Removing a background used to require Photoshop skills. Now it takes seconds online. Whether you need a transparent background for a logo, product photo or profile picture, here is how to do it free.</p>\n<h2>Why you need transparent backgrounds</h2>\n<ul><li>Product photos for eCommerce (white or transparent background)</li><li>Logos that work on any coloured background</li><li>Social media posts with clean, professional subjects</li><li>Presentation slides where the background clashes with slide colours</li></ul>\n<h2>What format to save in after removing background</h2>\n<p>Always save as <strong>PNG</strong> after removing the background. JPG does not support transparency — if you save as JPG, the transparent area becomes white. PNG or WebP are your only options for transparency.</p>\n<h2>Tips for clean background removal</h2>\n<ul><li>Start with a high-contrast photo — dark subject on light background (or vice versa) gives the cleanest cut</li><li>Avoid busy backgrounds with colours similar to your subject</li><li>For hair and fur, zoom in and check edges carefully before finalising</li><li>Product photos on a plain white background remove almost perfectly every time</li></ul>\n<h2>After removing the background</h2>\n<p>Once you have the transparent PNG, compress it using the <a href="/#/t/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a> with lossless compression to reduce file size. Then use the <a href="/#/t/watermark-image">Watermark tool</a> if you need to add branding before sharing.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What image types work best for background removal?</summary><p>Product photos on plain backgrounds, portrait photos on simple backgrounds, and logos. Busy scenes with overlapping colours are harder to process cleanly.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Can I remove background from a logo?</summary><p>Yes. Upload the logo as PNG for best results. If the logo has a white background, the remover will make it transparent — perfect for placing on dark or coloured backgrounds.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['create-gif-from-images']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-create-gif-from-images.html',title:'How to Create an Animated GIF From Images Free Online',date:'June 2026',read:'4 min',cat:'Converter Tools',excerpt:'Create animated GIFs from multiple images or video frames online. Set frame speed, loop settings and download instantly — no software, no sign-up.',html:'<p>Animated GIFs are one of the most shared formats on the internet — used in social media, email marketing, presentations and chat. Creating one used to require video editing software. Now you can do it in your browser.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/gif-maker" class="tool-cta-link">Create GIF Free →</a>\n<h2>Best uses for animated GIFs</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Social media</strong>: Twitter/X and LinkedIn support GIFs natively in posts</li><li><strong>Email marketing</strong>: Animated GIFs play in most email clients (except Outlook 2013–2016)</li><li><strong>Presentations</strong>: Add motion to PowerPoint or Google Slides without embedding video</li><li><strong>UI/UX prototypes</strong>: Show micro-interactions and transitions to clients</li><li><strong>Product demos</strong>: Show before/after, step-by-step or feature highlights</li></ul>\n<h2>Optimising GIF file size</h2>\n<p>GIFs are large compared to video. A 5-second GIF can easily reach 5–10MB. To keep file size manageable:</p>\n<ul><li>Keep dimensions small — 480px wide is usually enough for web</li><li>Reduce frame rate — 10–15 fps looks smooth for most content</li><li>Limit the colour palette — GIFs support max 256 colours</li><li>Keep duration under 5 seconds for email use (some clients block longer GIFs)</li></ul>\n<h2>GIF vs WebP vs MP4 — when to use each</h2>\n<p><strong>GIF</strong>: Use when you need universal compatibility. Works everywhere, no autoplay issues.</p>\n<p><strong>Animated WebP</strong>: 40–70% smaller than GIF at the same quality. Use the <a href="/#/t/gif-to-webp">GIF to WebP converter</a> to convert after creating.</p>\n<p><strong>MP4 video</strong>: Best for long animations. HTML video with autoplay+loop+muted mimics GIF behaviour at 90% smaller file size.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>How many frames do I need for a smooth GIF?</summary><p>At least 10 frames per second for smooth motion. For simple animations like logo reveals or icon transitions, even 5–8 frames can look smooth.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Why is my GIF so large?</summary><p>GIFs use an inefficient palette system. Limit colours, reduce dimensions and frame count. Or convert to WebP with the <a href="/#/t/gif-to-webp">GIF to WebP converter</a> for much smaller files.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['reduce-pdf-file-size']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-reduce-pdf-file-size.html',title:'How to Reduce PDF File Size Without Losing Quality',date:'June 2026',read:'5 min',cat:'PDF Tools',excerpt:'Compress PDF files online for free. Reduce PDF size for email attachments, web uploads and sharing without installing software.',html:'<p>A 50MB PDF that should be 2MB is one of the most common frustrations in office work. Email providers reject large attachments, clients struggle to open them, and web forms have size limits. Here is how to fix it.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/pdf-compressor" class="tool-cta-link">Compress PDF Free →</a>\n<h2>Why PDFs become large</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Embedded images</strong>: The biggest culprit. A PDF with high-resolution photos can easily exceed 50MB</li><li><strong>Embedded fonts</strong>: Some PDFs embed entire font files rather than just used characters</li><li><strong>Scan quality</strong>: Scanned documents at 600 DPI create enormous files</li><li><strong>Unoptimised export</strong>: Default export settings from Word, InDesign or Photoshop are often unnecessarily large</li></ul>\n<h2>How much can you compress a PDF?</h2>\n<p>Results vary significantly based on content. Image-heavy PDFs typically compress by 60–80%. Text-only PDFs may only compress 10–20% since text is already efficient. A 10MB brochure PDF commonly reduces to 2–3MB with no visible quality loss.</p>\n<h2>When NOT to compress</h2>\n<ul><li>Legal or archival documents where pixel-perfect quality is required</li><li>PDFs intended for professional printing (need full resolution images)</li><li>PDFs that will be further edited in Photoshop or Illustrator</li></ul>\n<h2>Other ways to reduce PDF size</h2>\n<p><strong>Remove unnecessary pages</strong>: Use the <a href="/#/t/pdf-page-remover">PDF Page Remover</a> to delete blank pages, cover pages or appendices before sharing.</p>\n<p><strong>Split the PDF</strong>: Use the <a href="/#/t/pdf-splitter">PDF Splitter</a> to send only the relevant section rather than the entire document.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What is the maximum PDF size for Gmail?</summary><p>Gmail allows attachments up to 25MB. For larger files, use Google Drive and share a link. Compress the PDF first with the <a href="/#/t/pdf-compressor">PDF Compressor</a> to stay under the limit.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Does compressing a PDF affect the text?</summary><p>No. Text compression is lossless — the text remains perfectly readable and searchable. Only image quality is affected when using lossy compression.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['create-qr-code-business']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-create-qr-code-business.html',title:'How to Create a QR Code for Your Business — Free Generator',date:'June 2026',read:'4 min',cat:'Converter Tools',excerpt:'Generate a free QR code for your website, menu, business card or social media. Download as high-resolution PNG. No sign-up, no watermarks.',html:'<p>QR codes have made a permanent comeback. Restaurant menus, business cards, product packaging, event posters — they appear everywhere. Generating one takes 10 seconds and costs nothing.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/qr-code-generator" class="tool-cta-link">Generate QR Code Free →</a>\n<h2>What can a QR code link to?</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Website URL</strong>: Direct visitors to your homepage or a specific landing page</li><li><strong>Google Maps</strong>: Link to your business location for easy navigation</li><li><strong>WhatsApp</strong>: Pre-fill a message to your business number</li><li><strong>PDF menu or brochure</strong>: Host on Google Drive and link to the share URL</li><li><strong>Social media profile</strong>: Instagram, LinkedIn, or any platform URL</li><li><strong>Payment link</strong>: UPI, PayPal, or Razorpay payment URLs</li><li><strong>Plain text</strong>: WiFi passwords, short instructions, contact information</li></ul>\n<h2>QR code size for print</h2>\n<p>Download at the highest resolution available. For print use:</p>\n<ul><li>Business card: minimum 2cm × 2cm (800px at 300 DPI)</li><li>A4 poster: minimum 4cm × 4cm</li><li>Outdoor banner: minimum 8cm × 8cm</li></ul>\n<p>Always test your printed QR code by scanning it before large print runs.</p>\n<h2>QR code best practices</h2>\n<ul><li>Always include a short URL hint below the QR code ("Scan to view menu")</li><li>Leave white space (quiet zone) around the code — do not crop edges</li><li>Test at the smallest size you plan to print it</li><li>Use a dark code on a white or light background (not the reverse)</li><li>For business use, use a URL shortener so you can change the destination without reprinting</li></ul>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>How long does a QR code last?</summary><p>Forever, if the URL it points to stays live. If the website goes down, the QR code stops working. Use a URL shortener (like bit.ly) so you can redirect the code even after printing.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Can I put a logo inside a QR code?</summary><p>QR codes have built-in error correction that allows up to 30% of the pattern to be obscured. A small logo in the centre works — but always test that it still scans reliably after adding the logo.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['best-free-tools-designers-2026']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-best-free-tools-designers-2026.html',title:'20 Best Free Online Tools for Graphic Designers in 2026',date:'June 2026',read:'7 min',cat:'Image Tools',excerpt:'The best free browser-based tools for graphic designers in 2026 — image editors, PDF tools, color palette generators, and marketing design tools. No downloads.',html:'<p>The best design tools used to cost hundreds of dollars per year. In 2026, a huge range of professional-grade tools run entirely free in your browser. Here are the most useful ones.</p>\n<h2>Image tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a></h3>\n<p>Reduce image file sizes by up to 80% without visible quality loss. Essential before uploading anything to a website or sending by email.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/image-resizer">Image Resizer</a></h3>\n<p>Resize to exact pixel dimensions or percentage. Batch process multiple images at once.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/social-image-resizer">Social Media Image Resizer</a></h3>\n<p>Resize any image for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter/X, LinkedIn, YouTube, Pinterest and more — all with drag-to-crop.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/watermark-image">Watermark Tool</a></h3>\n<p>Add a text or image watermark to protect your work before sharing portfolio images or client previews.</p>\n<h2>Color tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/color-palette-gen">Color Palette Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Extract a palette from any image OR generate complementary, analogous, and triadic palettes from a base colour. Get HEX, RGB, and HSL values.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/brand-color-extract">Brand Color Extractor</a></h3>\n<p>Upload a logo and extract the exact brand colours as CSS variables. Essential when starting a new client project.</p>\n<h2>PDF tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/pdf-merger">PDF Merger</a></h3>\n<p>Combine multiple PDFs into one. Reorder files before merging. No file size limits.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/pdf-compressor">PDF Compressor</a></h3>\n<p>Compress large PDF presentations and brochures for email and web delivery.</p>\n<h2>Marketing design tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/og-image-gen">OG Image Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Design 1200×630 Open Graph images for social media link previews. Text, brand colours, logo — download as PNG.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/cta-button-gen">CTA Button Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Design CTA buttons with live preview and copy the CSS directly. No Figma needed for simple button design tasks.</p>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>All tools on Tarumak Studio are 100% free, browser-based, and private. Your files never leave your device.</p></div>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Are browser-based design tools as good as Photoshop?</summary><p>For specific tasks — compression, resizing, format conversion, colour extraction — yes. For complex compositing, illustration, or multi-layer editing, dedicated software still has advantages. The tools above replace Photoshop for probably 80% of everyday design tasks.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['add-watermark-photos']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-add-watermark-photos.html',title:'How to Add a Watermark to Photos Online — Protect Your Work',date:'June 2026',read:'3 min',cat:'Image Tools',excerpt:'Add a text or image watermark to photos online for free. Adjust opacity, position and size. Protect your photography and design work before sharing.',html:'<p>Sharing your work online without a watermark risks others using it without credit or payment. A professional watermark takes 30 seconds to add and protects every image you share.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/watermark-image" class="tool-cta-link">Add Watermark Free →</a>\n<h2>Text vs image watermarks — which to use?</h2>\n<p><strong>Text watermarks</strong> are ideal for most use cases. Include your name, website, or Instagram handle. Simple, fast, and universally readable.</p>\n<p><strong>Image watermarks</strong> (your logo) look more professional and reinforce branding. Use a PNG with a transparent background for the best result.</p>\n<h2>Watermark positioning tips</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Bottom-right corner</strong>: The most common position. Visible but not intrusive</li><li><strong>Centre at 10–20% opacity</strong>: Harder to crop out, but affects the viewing experience. Use only for high-value work you want to protect strongly</li><li><strong>Multiple watermarks</strong>: A grid of watermarks across the image is the most effective protection but least professional looking</li></ul>\n<h2>Opacity settings</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>30–40% opacity</strong>: Clearly visible, professional-looking</li><li><strong>15–25% opacity</strong>: Subtle, for presentation portfolios where you still want the image to look clean</li><li><strong>50–70% opacity</strong>: Maximum protection for high-value images shared in public galleries</li></ul>\n<h2>Before sharing client previews</h2>\n<p>Always watermark client work before sharing mockups or previews. Clients sometimes share previews internally before payment is complete. A watermark ensures work cannot be used without your permission.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Can watermarks be removed?</summary><p>A corner watermark can be cropped. A semi-transparent watermark covering the image is much harder to remove. For maximum protection, cover the central subject area of the image with a semi-transparent watermark.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['free-favicon-generator']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-free-favicon-generator.html',title:'Free Favicon Generator — Create Website Favicons in All Sizes',date:'June 2026',read:'3 min',cat:'Developer Tools',excerpt:'Generate all required favicon sizes from any image online — 16x16 to 512x512 pixels. Download ICO, PNG and SVG formats instantly. Free, no sign-up.',html:'<p>A favicon is the small icon in the browser tab beside your site name. Without one, browsers show a generic puzzle piece or leaf icon — an immediate signal that a site is not professionally finished.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/favicon-generator" class="tool-cta-link">Generate Favicon Free →</a>\n<h2>All required favicon sizes in 2026</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>16×16 px</strong>: Browser tab</li><li><strong>32×32 px</strong>: Browser tab on high-DPI displays</li><li><strong>48×48 px</strong>: Windows shortcuts</li><li><strong>180×180 px</strong>: Apple Touch Icon (iPhone home screen)</li><li><strong>192×192 px</strong>: Android Chrome home screen</li><li><strong>512×512 px</strong>: PWA splash screen and Google search results</li></ul>\n<h2>How to add a favicon to your website</h2>\n<p>Add these lines inside your HTML <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> tag:</p>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>&lt;link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg"&gt;<br>&lt;link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/apple-touch-icon.png"&gt;<br>&lt;link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/favicon-32x32.png"&gt;</p></div>\n<h2>Favicon design tips</h2>\n<ul><li>Use a simple shape — a lettermark, symbol, or icon. Detail disappears at 16px</li><li>Avoid thin lines that become invisible at small sizes</li><li>High contrast between icon and background</li><li>Test at actual 16px size before finalising</li><li>SVG favicons work in all modern browsers and scale perfectly</li></ul>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Why is my new favicon not showing?</summary><p>Browsers cache favicons aggressively. Do a hard refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R on Windows, Cmd+Shift+R on Mac). You may also need to clear browser cache. It can take hours for all visitors to see the new favicon.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['hashtag-strategy-instagram']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-hashtag-strategy-instagram.html',title:'Hashtag Strategy for Instagram and Twitter in 2026 — Free Generator',date:'June 2026',read:'5 min',cat:'Marketing Designer',excerpt:'Learn the best hashtag strategy for Instagram and Twitter in 2026. How many hashtags to use, how to research them, and how to generate them free.',html:'<p>Hashtags done right can put your posts in front of thousands of people who have never heard of you. Done wrong, they look like spam and get your account suppressed. Here is what actually works in 2026.</p>\n<h2>How many hashtags to use in 2026</h2>\n<p><strong>Instagram</strong>: 3–5 highly relevant hashtags outperform 30 generic ones. Instagram\'s own data shows posts with 3–5 targeted hashtags get better reach than those with 20+. The algorithm now prioritises content relevance over hashtag volume.</p>\n<p><strong>Twitter/X</strong>: 1–2 maximum. More than 2 hashtags on Twitter reduces engagement by up to 17% according to published studies.</p>\n<p><strong>LinkedIn</strong>: 3–5 professional, topic-specific hashtags. Avoid generic tags like #business or #success — too broad to drive quality engagement.</p>\n<h2>Three types of hashtags to mix</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Niche hashtags</strong> (5,000–100,000 posts): Best for reaching engaged audiences. #FreelanceDesigner, #UIUXDesign, #BrandIdentityDesign</li><li><strong>Medium hashtags</strong> (100,000–500,000 posts): Moderate competition, good visibility. #GraphicDesign, #WebDesign, #LogoDesign</li><li><strong>Broad hashtags</strong> (1M+ posts): High competition, limited value. Use sparingly as one of your 3–5</li></ul>\n<h2>How to research hashtags</h2>\n<ol><li>Search your main keyword on Instagram and check the "Related" section</li><li>Look at what hashtags your top competitors use on their best-performing posts</li><li>Check hashtag size — aim for niche and medium tags, not oversaturated ones</li><li>Rotate hashtag sets to avoid being flagged as repetitive</li></ol>\n<h2>Hashtags for designers</h2>\n<p>High-performing design hashtags: #UIDesign #UXDesign #BrandDesign #FreelanceDesigner #DesignerLife #GraphicDesigner #LogoDesigner #DigitalMarketing #CreativeDirection #DesignInspiration</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Do hashtags still work in 2026?</summary><p>Yes, but the strategy has shifted. Fewer, more targeted hashtags now outperform large hashtag lists. Instagram\'s algorithm now uses semantic understanding of post content — hashtags supplement this but no longer drive it.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['meta-tags-seo-guide']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-meta-tags-seo-guide.html',title:'Meta Tags for SEO — Complete Guide with Examples (2026)',date:'June 2026',read:'6 min',cat:'Developer Tools',excerpt:'Learn how to write title tags, meta descriptions, and Open Graph tags for better SEO and social media sharing. Includes examples and character limits.',html:'<p>Meta tags are the first thing Google and social media platforms read about your page. Getting them right can be the difference between ranking on page 1 and being invisible. This guide covers every tag that matters.</p>\n<h2>Title tag — the most important SEO element</h2>\n<p>The title tag appears in search results as the clickable blue headline. It is the single most important on-page SEO element.</p>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>&lt;title&gt;Free Image Compressor Online — Reduce Size Without Losing Quality | Tarumak Studio&lt;/title&gt;</p></div>\n<ul><li><strong>Length</strong>: 50–60 characters (Google truncates at ~580px width)</li><li><strong>Format</strong>: Primary keyword | Secondary keyword | Brand name</li><li>Put the primary keyword first — Google gives more weight to words near the start</li><li>Unique title for every page — never duplicate titles</li></ul>\n<h2>Meta description — controls your click-through rate</h2>\n<p>The meta description appears under the title in search results. It does not directly affect rankings but significantly affects click-through rate (CTR).</p>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>&lt;meta name="description" content="Compress JPG, PNG and WebP images online for free. Reduce file size by up to 80% without visible quality loss — all in your browser, no uploads required."&gt;</p></div>\n<ul><li><strong>Length</strong>: 120–160 characters</li><li>Include the primary keyword naturally</li><li>Write it as an ad — it should make people want to click</li><li>Include a benefit or unique selling point</li></ul>\n<h2>Open Graph tags — for social media sharing</h2>\n<p>OG tags control how your page looks when shared on Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn and WhatsApp. Without them, social platforms guess — often badly.</p>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>&lt;meta property="og:title" content="Your Page Title"&gt;<br>&lt;meta property="og:description" content="Your description"&gt;<br>&lt;meta property="og:image" content="https://yoursite.com/og-image.png"&gt;<br>&lt;meta property="og:url" content="https://yoursite.com/page"&gt;</p></div>\n<p>Create your OG image (1200×630 px) using the free <a href="/#/t/og-image-gen">OG Image Generator</a>.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Does meta description affect rankings?</summary><p>Not directly. Google sometimes ignores your meta description and writes its own based on page content. But a well-written meta description improves CTR, which signals relevance and can indirectly improve rankings.</p></details>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What is the canonical tag?</summary><p>&lt;link rel="canonical" href="..."&gt; tells Google which URL is the "original" version of a page. Use it when the same content appears at multiple URLs to prevent duplicate content issues.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['pdf-to-jpg-convert']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-pdf-to-jpg-convert.html',title:'How to Convert PDF to JPG Online — Free, Fast and Private',date:'June 2026',read:'3 min',cat:'PDF Tools',excerpt:'Convert PDF pages to JPG images online for free. Extract all pages or specific pages as high-quality JPG images — no software download, no uploads.',html:'<p>Sometimes you need an image version of a PDF — for a presentation, social media post, email, or to share a single page with someone who cannot open PDFs. Converting PDF to JPG takes seconds.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/pdf-to-jpg" class="tool-cta-link">Convert PDF to JPG Free →</a>\n<h2>When you need PDF to JPG conversion</h2>\n<ul><li>Sharing a specific page from a report on social media</li><li>Inserting a PDF page into a PowerPoint or Google Slides presentation</li><li>Sending a single page from a contract or document by email or WhatsApp</li><li>Creating a preview image of a PDF brochure for a website</li><li>Editing a PDF page in an image editor</li></ul>\n<h2>Quality tips for PDF to JPG conversion</h2>\n<p>The quality of the output JPG depends on the PDF renderer. For best results:</p>\n<ul><li>Keep the original PDF at the highest quality (do not compress it before converting)</li><li>If the output looks blurry, the source PDF may have low-resolution images embedded in it — this cannot be improved by the converter</li><li>Text in the output JPG is rasterised (becomes pixels) — if you need editable text, use PDF to Text instead</li></ul>\n<h2>Alternative: PDF to PNG for transparency</h2>\n<p>If the PDF has a white background you want to make transparent (for example, a logo or diagram on a white page), convert to PNG instead. PNG supports transparency where JPG does not. Use the <a href="/#/t/pdf-to-jpg">PDF to JPG tool</a> which also outputs PNG format.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Can I convert a multi-page PDF to separate JPG images?</summary><p>Yes. The converter extracts each page as a separate JPG image. You can then download them all at once or individually.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['color-palette-brand-guide']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-color-palette-brand-guide.html',title:'How to Create a Brand Color Palette — Complete Guide for Designers',date:'June 2026',read:'6 min',cat:'Marketing Designer',excerpt:'Learn how to create a professional brand color palette from scratch. Color psychology, palette types, extraction from logos, and CSS variables guide.',html:'<p>A brand color palette is the foundation of visual identity. The right colors make a brand instantly recognisable — think of Coca-Cola red or WhatsApp green. Here is how to build one professionally.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/color-palette-gen" class="tool-cta-link">Generate Color Palette Free →</a>\n<h2>How many colors does a brand palette need?</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Primary color</strong>: 1 color — your main brand color, used most frequently</li><li><strong>Secondary colors</strong>: 2–3 colors — support the primary in design compositions</li><li><strong>Neutral colors</strong>: 2–3 — grays, off-whites, blacks for text and backgrounds</li><li><strong>Accent color</strong>: 1 — a contrasting pop color for CTAs and highlights</li></ul>\n<h2>Color psychology for brands</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Blue</strong>: Trust, professionalism, technology — banks, SaaS, healthcare</li><li><strong>Green</strong>: Growth, nature, health, money — finance, wellness, sustainability</li><li><strong>Orange/Red</strong>: Energy, urgency, appetite — food, retail, CTAs</li><li><strong>Purple</strong>: Premium, creativity, wisdom — luxury, education, beauty</li><li><strong>Black</strong>: Sophistication, luxury, power — fashion, automotive, premium</li><li><strong>Yellow</strong>: Optimism, warmth, caution — consumer brands, children, warnings</li></ul>\n<h2>Extracting colors from a logo</h2>\n<p>Already have a logo? Upload it to the <a href="/#/t/brand-color-extract">Brand Color Extractor</a> to get the exact HEX, RGB, and HSL values of every color in the design. This is essential when onboarding a new client — you get their brand colors in seconds.</p>\n<h2>Generating harmonious color schemes</h2>\n<p>Start with your primary color and use color theory to generate a full palette:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Complementary</strong>: Opposite on the color wheel — high contrast, energetic</li><li><strong>Analogous</strong>: Adjacent colors — harmonious, cohesive, calming</li><li><strong>Triadic</strong>: Three equidistant colors — vibrant, diverse, balanced</li></ul>\n<p>Use the <a href="/#/t/color-palette-gen">Color Palette Generator</a> to visualise all these schemes from any base color.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>How do I save brand colors as CSS variables?</summary><p>Use the <a href="/#/t/brand-color-extract">Brand Color Extractor</a> to extract colors and download them as CSS custom properties (--brand-primary, --brand-secondary etc.) ready to paste into your stylesheet.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['instagram-story-size-guide']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-instagram-story-size-guide.html',title:'Instagram Story Size 2026 — Dimensions, Templates and Best Practices',date:'June 2026',read:'4 min',cat:'Marketing Designer',excerpt:'Instagram Story size guide for 2026: 1080x1920 pixels, safe zones, text placement, and tips for higher engagement. Free story image resizer included.',html:'<p>Instagram Stories get 500 million daily viewers. Getting the dimensions right means your content fills the screen beautifully instead of showing awkward white bars or cropped edges.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/social-image-resizer" class="tool-cta-link">Resize for Instagram Story Free →</a>\n<h2>Instagram Story dimensions 2026</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Size</strong>: 1080 × 1920 pixels (9:16 aspect ratio)</li><li><strong>File format</strong>: JPG or PNG for images, MP4 or MOV for video</li><li><strong>Maximum file size</strong>: 30MB for images, 4GB for video</li><li><strong>Safe zone</strong>: Keep important content in the central 1080 × 1420 px area to avoid being covered by UI elements</li></ul>\n<h2>Understanding the safe zone</h2>\n<p>Instagram overlays UI on top and bottom of Stories:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Top 250px</strong>: Username, profile photo, close button overlay — keep this area clear</li><li><strong>Bottom 250px</strong>: "Send message" bar and swipe-up area — keep this area clear</li><li><strong>Safe zone</strong>: The central 1080 × 1420 px region — place all key text and visuals here</li></ul>\n<h2>Story design best practices</h2>\n<ul><li>Use large, bold text — Stories are viewed on mobile screens at arm\'s length</li><li>Keep text in the safe zone, away from the top and bottom 250px</li><li>Use high-contrast colors — white text on dark background or dark text on light background</li><li>Include a clear CTA — "Swipe Up", "Link in Bio", "DM for details"</li><li>First 1–2 seconds determine if viewers watch the whole Story — make them count</li></ul>\n<h2>Instagram Reels cover image</h2>\n<p>Reels use the same 1080 × 1920 px format. The cover image (thumbnail) is cropped to 1080 × 1350 px when shown in the grid. Design your cover with this in mind.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Can I use a landscape image in an Instagram Story?</summary><p>Yes, but it will show with black bars above and below on most phones. Instagram sometimes auto-adds a blurred version of the image as a background fill. For best results, always use 9:16 format.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['how-to-merge-pdfs']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-how-to-merge-pdfs.html',title:'How to Merge PDF Files Online — Free, No Software, No Sign-Up',date:'June 2026',read:'3 min',cat:'PDF Tools',excerpt:'Merge multiple PDF files into one document online for free. Drag to reorder, combine unlimited PDFs, download instantly. Browser-based, files never uploaded.',html:'<p>Combining PDFs is one of the most common document tasks — merging a cover letter with a CV, combining chapters of a report, or combining signed pages into one file. You do not need Acrobat or any paid software.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/pdf-merger" class="tool-cta-link">Merge PDFs Free →</a>\n<h2>Step by step: how to merge PDFs</h2>\n<ol><li>Open the <a href="/#/t/pdf-merger">PDF Merger tool</a></li><li>Click "Upload" or drag your PDF files into the drop zone</li><li>Drag the file cards to set the order (the first card becomes page 1)</li><li>Click "Merge PDFs"</li><li>Download the combined PDF</li></ol>\n<h2>How many PDFs can I combine?</h2>\n<p>There is no limit on the number of files. The practical limit is your computer\'s available memory. Most computers handle 50+ PDFs without issue. For very large PDF collections (hundreds of files), merge in batches.</p>\n<h2>Maintaining page order</h2>\n<p>The tool merges PDFs in the order you upload or arrange them. If you need to rearrange individual pages (not just files), use the <a href="/#/t/pdf-organizer">PDF Organizer</a> which shows a thumbnail of every page for precise control.</p>\n<h2>Are merged PDFs secure?</h2>\n<p>Your files process entirely in your browser. They are never uploaded to any server, never stored, and never seen by anyone else. You can merge sensitive legal or financial documents with complete privacy.</p>\n<h2>Related PDF tools</h2>\n<div class="art-tools"><a href="/#/t/pdf-splitter">Split PDF</a><a href="/#/t/pdf-organizer">Reorder Pages</a><a href="/#/t/pdf-compressor">Compress PDF</a><a href="/#/t/pdf-page-remover">Remove Pages</a></div>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What if my PDFs are password-protected?</summary><p>Remove the password first using the <a href="/#/t/pdf-unlock">PDF Unlock tool</a>, then merge. Note: you need to know the password to unlock the PDF.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['best-free-marketing-tools']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-best-free-marketing-tools.html',title:'Best Free Marketing Tools for Designers and Creators in 2026',date:'June 2026',read:'7 min',cat:'Marketing Designer',excerpt:'The best free marketing tools for designers and content creators in 2026 — social media resizer, UTM builder, OG image generator, ad copy generator and more.',html:'<p>Marketing tools used to mean expensive subscriptions. In 2026, every tool a designer or marketer needs for campaigns, social media, and content creation runs free in the browser. Here are the most useful ones.</p>\n<h2>Social media image tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/social-image-resizer">Social Media Image Resizer</a></h3>\n<p>Resize any image to exact platform dimensions for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter/X, LinkedIn, YouTube, Pinterest and WhatsApp. Drag-to-crop, multiple modes. The single most-used marketing tool for any designer.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/og-image-gen">Open Graph Image Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Create 1200×630 OG images for link previews on social media. Add title text, brand colours and a logo — download as PNG. Essential for content marketers and bloggers.</p>\n<h2>Campaign and analytics tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/utm-builder">UTM Link Builder</a></h3>\n<p>Build UTM-tagged campaign URLs for Google Analytics 4. Also decodes existing UTM links. Absolutely essential for tracking what actually drives website traffic.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/ad-copy-gen">Ad Copy Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Generate headlines, body copy and CTAs for Facebook, Google and Instagram ads. Template-based — no AI subscription needed.</p>\n<h2>Brand and design tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/color-palette-gen">Color Palette Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Extract color palettes from images or generate harmonious color schemes. Ideal for maintaining brand consistency across campaigns.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/brand-color-extract">Brand Color Extractor</a></h3>\n<p>Upload a client\'s logo and extract the exact brand colors as HEX, RGB, HSL and CSS variables in seconds.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/cta-button-gen">CTA Button Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Design call-to-action buttons with live preview and download as PNG or copy the CSS. Great for landing page prototypes and client presentations.</p>\n<h2>Lead generation tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/pdf-lead-magnet">PDF Lead Magnet Creator</a></h3>\n<p>Build professional PDF checklists, guides and cheatsheets to grow an email list. Choose template style, add brand colours, download instantly.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What is the most important free marketing tool?</summary><p>For most marketing designers, the Social Media Image Resizer and UTM Builder provide the most daily value. Image resizing is needed for every campaign; UTM tracking shows what actually works.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['free-tools-freelancers']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-free-tools-freelancers.html',title:'Free Online Tools Every Freelancer Needs in 2026',date:'June 2026',read:'6 min',cat:'Image Tools',excerpt:'The essential free browser-based tools for freelancers in 2026 — image compressors, PDF tools, marketing assets, invoice tools, and productivity apps.',html:'<p>Freelancing means wearing every hat. Designer, marketer, accountant, and customer support — all in one day. The right free tools save hours every week. Here are the ones worth bookmarking.</p>\n<h2>Client-facing design tools</h2>\n<h3>Image compression (<a href="/#/t/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a>)</h3>\n<p>Compress images before sending deliverables by email or uploading to client portals. A 50MB folder of images becomes 5MB without visible quality loss.</p>\n<h3>Watermarking (<a href="/#/t/watermark-image">Watermark Tool</a>)</h3>\n<p>Always watermark preview images before client approval. Protects work until payment is received.</p>\n<h3>PDF merger (<a href="/#/t/pdf-merger">PDF Merger</a>)</h3>\n<p>Combine deliverables, proposals, and contracts into single PDFs for professional client delivery.</p>\n<h2>Marketing your freelance business</h2>\n<h3>Social media content (<a href="/#/t/social-image-resizer">Social Image Resizer</a>)</h3>\n<p>Resize portfolio pieces for every platform without manual cropping in Photoshop.</p>\n<h3>Campaign tracking (<a href="/#/t/utm-builder">UTM Builder</a>)</h3>\n<p>If you are running any ads or sharing links to your portfolio, UTM parameters tell you exactly which sources drive enquiries.</p>\n<h3>Lead magnets (<a href="/#/t/pdf-lead-magnet">PDF Lead Magnet Creator</a>)</h3>\n<p>Create a free checklist or guide as an email capture tool. "10 questions to ask before hiring a designer" type resources work extremely well.</p>\n<h2>Brand consistency tools</h2>\n<h3>Color extraction (<a href="/#/t/brand-color-extract">Brand Color Extractor</a>)</h3>\n<p>Upload a client\'s logo at the start of every project and extract their exact brand colors as CSS variables. Takes 10 seconds, saves hours of guessing.</p>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>All tools on Tarumak Studio are completely free, browser-based, and private. Your files never leave your device — essential when handling client confidential materials.</p></div>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What is the best free tool for freelance designers?</summary><p>The Image Compressor and PDF Merger solve the most common daily problems. The Brand Color Extractor and Social Image Resizer are close runners-up for client work efficiency.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['convert-jpg-to-pdf']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-convert-jpg-to-pdf.html',title:'How to Convert JPG to PDF Online — Free and Instant',date:'June 2026',read:'3 min',cat:'PDF Tools',excerpt:'Convert JPG images to PDF online for free. Combine multiple JPGs into one PDF or convert individually. Browser-based, no uploads, instant download.',html:'<p>Converting JPG images to PDF is one of the most common document tasks — for scanned documents, photo portfolios, or turning screenshots into a shareable PDF. No software required.</p>\n<a href="/#/t/jpg-to-pdf" class="tool-cta-link">Convert JPG to PDF Free →</a>\n<h2>Common reasons to convert JPG to PDF</h2>\n<ul><li>Combining multiple scanned document pages into one PDF</li><li>Creating a PDF portfolio from JPEG images</li><li>Converting screenshots into a shareable PDF report</li><li>Sending photos as a professional document (not a raw image file)</li><li>Combining before-and-after design images for client presentation</li></ul>\n<h2>How to combine multiple JPGs into one PDF</h2>\n<ol><li>Open the <a href="/#/t/jpg-to-pdf">JPG to PDF converter</a></li><li>Upload multiple JPG images at once</li><li>Drag to reorder if needed</li><li>Click "Convert to PDF"</li><li>Download the single PDF containing all images</li></ol>\n<h2>Image quality in the PDF</h2>\n<p>The converter maintains the original quality of your JPG images inside the PDF. The output quality equals the input quality — if your source image is sharp, the PDF will be sharp.</p>\n<h2>Related: images to PDF from multiple formats</h2>\n<p>If you have a mix of JPG, PNG, and WebP images, use the <a href="/#/t/images-to-pdf">Images to PDF tool</a> which accepts all common image formats in a single conversion.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>What is the maximum image size for JPG to PDF conversion?</summary><p>There is no artificial file size limit. The practical limit depends on your browser and available memory. For very large images (50MB+), processing may take a few seconds longer.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['web-design-tools-2026']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-web-design-tools-2026.html',title:'Best Free Web Design Tools in 2026 — No Subscription Needed',date:'June 2026',read:'6 min',cat:'Developer Tools',excerpt:'The best free web design tools in 2026 — CSS generators, color tools, favicon makers, image optimisers, and developer utilities. All browser-based.',html:'<p>Web design in 2026 benefits from an extraordinary range of free tools. Whether you are designing, building, or optimising a website, most of what you need runs free in your browser.</p>\n<h2>Image optimisation tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a></h3>\n<p>Essential for every web project. Compress JPG, PNG and WebP images before uploading. Speeds up your site and improves Core Web Vitals scores for better SEO.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/jpg-to-webp">JPG to WebP Converter</a></h3>\n<p>Convert images to WebP format for 25–35% smaller file sizes with the same visual quality. Supported by all modern browsers since 2020.</p>\n<h2>Color and design tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/color-palette-gen">Color Palette Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Generate complementary, analogous, and triadic color schemes from any base color. Extract palettes from images. Essential for CSS design system creation.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/brand-color-extract">Brand Color Extractor</a></h3>\n<p>Extract HEX, RGB, and HSL values from any logo or image. Download as CSS custom properties ready to paste into your stylesheet.</p>\n<h2>Favicon and icon tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/favicon-generator">Favicon Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Generate all required favicon sizes (16×16 to 512×512) from any image. Download all formats — ICO, PNG, SVG — in one click.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/qr-code-generator">QR Code Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Generate QR codes for web URLs, WiFi credentials, or contact information. Download as high-resolution PNG for print or web use.</p>\n<h2>Social and sharing tools</h2>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/og-image-gen">Open Graph Image Generator</a></h3>\n<p>Create 1200×630 OG images for social media link previews. Every web project needs one — without it, social shares show no preview image.</p>\n<h3><a href="/#/t/utm-builder">UTM Link Builder</a></h3>\n<p>Build UTM-tracked URLs for every campaign. Essential for measuring which traffic sources drive results.</p>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Do I still need Photoshop for web design?</summary><p>For most web design tasks in 2026 — image compression, format conversion, color extraction, favicon creation, OG image design — browser tools are faster and more convenient than Photoshop. For complex compositing or photo retouching, dedicated software still has advantages.</p></details>'};
ARTICLES['pdf-guide-2026']={url:'https://tarumakstudio.com/article-pdf-guide-2026.html',title:'Complete PDF Guide 2026 — Merge, Split, Compress, Convert and More',date:'June 2026',read:'8 min',cat:'PDF Tools',excerpt:'The complete guide to working with PDF files in 2026. How to merge, split, compress, convert, password-protect and extract content from PDFs free online.',html:'<p>PDF is the most universally used document format — but working with PDFs used to require expensive software. In 2026, every PDF task can be done free in your browser. Here is a complete reference guide.</p>\n<h2>Merging PDFs</h2>\n<p>Combining multiple PDFs into one is the most common PDF task. The <a href="/#/t/pdf-merger">PDF Merger</a> lets you upload multiple files, drag to reorder, and download a single combined PDF. No page or file number limits.</p>\n<h2>Splitting PDFs</h2>\n<p>Extract specific pages or split a PDF into individual page files using the <a href="/#/t/pdf-splitter">PDF Splitter</a>. Enter page ranges like "1-3, 7, 10-15" to extract exactly what you need.</p>\n<h2>Compressing PDFs</h2>\n<p>The <a href="/#/t/pdf-compressor">PDF Compressor</a> reduces file size by rasterising pages at reduced quality. Image-heavy PDFs typically shrink by 60–80%. Text-only PDFs compress less (10–20%) since text is already efficient.</p>\n<h2>Converting PDFs</h2>\n<ul><li><a href="/#/t/pdf-to-jpg">PDF to JPG</a>: Extract each page as a separate image</li><li><a href="/#/t/pdf-to-text">PDF to Text</a>: Extract all text content as a .txt file</li><li><a href="/#/t/jpg-to-pdf">JPG to PDF</a>: Convert images to PDF documents</li><li><a href="/#/t/images-to-pdf">Images to PDF</a>: Combine multiple images into one PDF</li></ul>\n<h2>Organising PDF pages</h2>\n<p>The <a href="/#/t/pdf-organizer">PDF Organizer</a> shows thumbnail previews of every page. Drag to reorder, rotate individual pages, and download the reorganised document. Far better than guessing page numbers.</p>\n<h2>Security</h2>\n<ul><li><a href="/#/t/pdf-password-protect">Password Protect PDF</a>: Add encryption before sharing sensitive documents</li><li><a href="/#/t/pdf-unlock">Unlock PDF</a>: Remove password from a PDF you own</li></ul>\n<div class="art-callout"><p>All 15 Tarumak Studio PDF tools are completely free, browser-based, and private. Your files never leave your device — essential for legal, financial, and confidential documents.</p></div>\n<details class="art-faq"><summary>Which PDF tool should I use first?</summary><p>If you have a large PDF you need to email, start with the PDF Compressor. If you need to combine documents, use the PDF Merger. If you need to extract a specific section, use the PDF Splitter.</p></details>'};

